1.2 **“Derivative Work”** means any modification of, adaptation of, or work based upon the Software, including any translation, abridgement, or other form in which the Software may be recast, transformed, or adapted.

1.3 **“Non‑Commercial Use”** means any use that (a) is undertaken primarily for the purposes of academic study, education or not‑for‑profit scientific research, and (b) for which neither the Licensee nor any third party receives direct or indirect compensation, monetary or otherwise, including but not limited to licence fees, service fees, advertising revenue, or the sale of data or models incorporating the Software.

1.4 **“Commercial Use”** means any use that does not qualify as Non‑Commercial Use, including but not limited to use in connection with any commercial, industrial or profit‑generating activity.

1.5 **“Licensee”** ("you") means any individual or legal entity exercising rights under this License.

1.6 **“Licensor”** means Mohamed Elnahla, the owner of all intellectual‑property rights in and to the Software.

